The evidence with the title 'Poverty hits twice as many British households as 30 years ago ... ' says Jun 18, 2014  ... Other figures being published include the claims that 5.5 million adults go without essential clothing ; that 2.5 million children live in damp homes; that 1.5 million children live in households that cannot afford to heat them; that one in four adults have incomes below what they themselves consider is needed  ... 
